{
  "stem": "1338.6",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so for them to send me to college and maintain me and my mother for four years, I felt that I will owe them my life.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had no right to take it if I was not convinced that I'll stay the rest of my life, which I was not.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I would have to study subjects that are useful for the kibbutz, which is mechanical engineering or civil.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that's about-- I don't know what events I want to relay.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You have something?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Yeah, let's skip ahead to how you got to America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I went to-- we left the kibbutz in '46-- '47, January.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we-- and I studied, and I got to Technion in '47, in October.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the partition decision in the United Nations was in November.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were drafted, practically immediately.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For a while, we were sort of [NON-ENGLISH] kind of thing for three months.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they marched, they closed the University.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I went to war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would like to say something about-- you asked me a question before we started, how does an immigrant and how, as an immigrant, as a permanent immigrant in so many places, how did I feel, how was I treated?",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Immigrants are never treated well.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They are never-- nobody understands an immigrant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm very sensitive to that when I see others.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the one thing that I owe Israel, and I will never forget-- never-- and that is, in the quest for normalcy, they gave me a gun, and they let me participate in a war as a soldier in a free country.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was the most significant catharsis of my problem of quest for normalcy.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
